	=== Bézout's identity
	For #mi(`a \neq`), #mi(`b \neq 0`), then #mi(`d=gcd(a,b)`) is the smallest positive integer for which there are integer solutions to
	#mitex(`ax+by=d`)
	If #mi(`(x,y)`) is one solution, then all solutions are given by
	#mitex(`\left(x+\frac{kb}{\gcd(a,b)}, y-\frac{ka}{\gcd(a,b)}\right), \quad k\in\mathbb{Z}`)

